<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9CFFB2C9C0FD96FE71B60B" bold="true" box="[136,463,597,624]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9CFFB2C887FD95FD67B614" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[463,729,598,624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9CFFB2C887FD95FD67B614" box="[463,729,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Euphorbia ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a worldwide tropical and subtropical weed. In the State of 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF9CFFB2CCC9FD95FF76B6F6" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
the species is very common, mainly on disturbed areas.
</paragraph>
